    • Method Detail

      • computeStats

        public static <T extends Rangeable,R extends CoverageRegion<T>> Collector<R,CoverageStatsCombiner,CoverageMapStats> computeStats()
        Returns a Collector that accumulates the input elements of a CoverageMap into a new CoverageMapStats.
        API Note:
          CoverageMapStats stats = coverageMap.regions()
					.parallel()
					.collect(CoverageMapCollectors.computeStats());
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of each element in the CoverageMap.
        R - the type of CoverageRegion in the coverageMap.
        Returns:
        a new CoverageMapStats Collector

      • toCoverageMap

        public static <T extends Rangeable> Collector<T,List<T>,CoverageMap<T>> toCoverageMap()
        Returns a Collector that accumulates the input elements into a new CoverageMap.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the input elements which must implement the Rangeable interface.
        Returns:
        a Collector which collects all the input elements into a CoverageMap.

      • toCoverageMap

        public static <T extends Rangeable> Collector<T,List<T>,CoverageMap<T>> toCoverageMap(int maxCoverage)
        Returns a Collector that accumulates the input elements into a new CoverageMap that has limited each coverage region to the specified maxCoverage. Any elements that provide additional coverage than the specified max will not be included in the CoverageMap.
        Implementation Note:
        filtering parallel streams may return CoverageMaps which contain different elements or even have different levels of coverage at certain coverage regions. This is because the max coverage filter is partially based on encounter order
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the input elements which must implement the Rangeable interface.
        Parameters:
        maxCoverage - the maxCoverage any CoverageRegion will be allowed to have; must be ≥ 0.
        Returns:
        a Collector which collects all the input elements into a CoverageMap.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if maxCoverage < 0.
        See Also:
        CoverageMapBuilder.maxAllowedCoverage(int)

      • toCoverageMap

        public static <T extends Rangeable> Collector<T,List<T>,CoverageMap<T>> toCoverageMap(int preferredMaxCoverage,
                                                                                      int requiredMinCoverage)
        Returns a Collector that accumulates the input elements into a new CoverageMap that will try to keep preferred maximum coverage depth any CoverageRegion in the resulting CoverageMap will have while still maintaining the required minimum coverage.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the input elements which must implement the Rangeable interface.
        Parameters:
        preferredMaxCoverage - the maximum coverage any CoverageRegion will strive to have; must be ≥ 0.
        requiredMinCoverage - the minimum coverage any CoverageRegion must have even at the expense of exceeding the preferredMaxCoverage; must be ≥ 0.
        Returns:
        a Collector which collects all the input elements into a CoverageMap.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if either parameter is < 0
        See Also:
        CoverageMapBuilder.maxAllowedCoverage(int, int)
